2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper focuses on the performance analysis of protograph LDPC codes over Nakagami-m fading relay channels, which is a topic related to communication and networking. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the performance of LDPC codes in relay channels, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper analyzes the performance of a system (i.e., the protograph LDPC codes) in a specific channel (i.e., Nakagami-m fading relay channels), which is a topic related to systems and control. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): Although less likely, the paper may also be related to game theory as it involves analyzing the performance of a coding scheme in a specific channel.
